Currently, when an SLA is reconfigured, the impacted issues may loose their SLA completely, e.g. when an issue is in a state between the "start counting" event and the "stop counting" event. Since there's good possibility the start counting event cannot be triggered again, these issue will remain without SLA, which is most probably not the wanted behavior (it is not for us...). 

Please re-vise the SLA reconfigure behavior, especially taking into account impacted issues and the re-configure options for these.

